<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 10:14PM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF NORTH CENTRAL MORTON
COUNTY THROUGH 1045 PM CDT...
At 1013 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Almont, or 31
miles west of Mandan, moving southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Almont around 1020 PM CDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
